curl -XPOST 'http://localhost:9200/electronic_products/_create/13126' -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"product_name": "SGM820xQ", "table_name": "PIN DESCRIPTION", "content": "PIN DESCRIPTION  PIN  NAME  TYPE  FUNCTION  1  VCC  I  Supply Voltage Pin. It is recommended to place a 0.1μF ceramic capacitor close to this pin.  2  CWD  I  Programmable Watchdog Timeout Input Pin. Connecting the CWD pin to GND via a capacitor to  set the adjustable watchdog timeout. Connecting the CWD pin to VCC via a 10kΩ resistor or  leaving it unconnected to select two different kinds of the preset watchdog timeout.  3  nMR  I  Manual Reset Input Pin. It is an active-low reset input with internal pull-up current.  4  GND  G  Ground.  5  SET  I  Logic Input Pin. Connecting the SET pin to GND will disable the watchdog timer. If nRESET is  deaseerted, the wactchdog can be enabled when SET is high.  6  WDI  I  Watchdog Input Pin. The WDI falling edge must appear within the timeout (tWD) period. When  nWDO or nRESET is low and the watchdog is disabled, WDI will be ignored. Note that this pin  cannot be left floating.  7  nWDO  O  Watchdog Open-Drain Output Pin. It is recommended to connect a resistor from 1kΩ to 10kΩ to  the rail. If the watchdog timeout occurs, the nWDO goes low for an nRESET timeout delay (tRST).  8  nRESET  O  Active-Low Open-Drain Reset Output Pin. It is recommended to connect a resistor from 1kΩ to  10kΩ to the rail. nRESET remains low if VCC is below the under-voltage threshold (VITN). And it  goes high when VCC exceeds VITN + VHYS after nRESET delay time (tRST).  Exposed  Pad  EP  G  Exposed Pad. This pad is not connected to internal circuit.    NOTE: I: Input; O: Output; G: Ground.       High-Accuracy Supervisory Circuit  SGM820xQ  with Integrated Watchdog Timer      6  DECEMBER 2023  SG Micro Corp  www.sg-micro.com  "}'
